# 🧠 Concept 2: Base Case (MOST IMPORTANT PART)

## ✅ What it is

👉 Base case is the **stopping condition**

Without it:
❌ infinite recursion
❌ stack overflow

---

## 💡 Real-World Analogy

Imagine:
You keep photocopying papers endlessly 📄

Eventually:
👉 machine crashes

Same in recursion.

---

## ⚙️ Why Base Case Matters

```c id="obg4u8"
if(n == 0)
    return;
```

👉 This tells recursion:
“STOP here.”

---

# ⚠️ MOST COMMON INTERVIEW QUESTION

## What happens if base case is missing?

👉 Function keeps calling itself forever.

Result:
❌ Stack Overflow Error

---

# 💻 Example Without Base Case

```c id="tbdm72"
void fun() {
    fun();
}
```

👉 Crashes eventually.

---

# 🔥 Call Stack Understanding (VERY IMPORTANT)

When recursion happens:

```id="0y4fup"
main()
  hello(3)
    hello(2)
      hello(1)
        hello(0)
```

Each call is stacked in memory.

👉 Last call finishes first.

This is:

## LIFO

(Last In First Out)

Same as:
📚 stack of plates

